```xml
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<manifest xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    package="com.aizenith568964.tiktok-automation-tool">

    <!-- Application metadata -->
    <application
        android:allowBackup="true"
        android:icon="@mipmap/ic_launcher"
        android:label="TikTok automation tool - Android Automation Tool"
        android:roundIcon="@mipmap/ic_launcher_round"
        android:supportsRtl="true"
        android:theme="@style/Theme.AppCompat.Light.NoActionBar">
        
        <!-- Main activity for the application -->
        <activity
            android:name=".MainActivity"
            android:exported="true">
            <intent-filter>
                <action android:name="android.intent.action.MAIN" />
                <category android:name="android.intent.category.LAUNCHER" />
            </intent-filter>
        </activity>

        <!-- Service for handling automation tasks -->
        <service
            android:name=".AutomationService"
            android:exported="false" />
    </application>

    <!-- Permissions required for the application -->
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.INTERNET" />
    <!-- Permission to access the internet for automated operations and management -->
    
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE" />
    <!-- Permission to check network connectivity status for uninterrupted operation -->
    
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE" />
    <!-- Permission to write to external storage for data management and logging -->
    
    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE" />
    <!-- Permission to read from external storage for accessing user content and settings -->

    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.FOREGROUND_SERVICE" />
    <!-- Permission to run foreground service required for continuous background operations -->

</manifest>
```

### Explanation of Key Components:
- **Application Tag**: This encapsulates the entire app configuration and includes metadata such as the app icon, label, and theme.
- **MainActivity**: This is the entry point of the app where users will interact with the main interface of the TikTok automation tool.
- **AutomationService**: A background service that handles automation tasks, ensuring that operations can run continuously without user intervention.
- **Permissions**: Necessary permissions are declared to allow the app to access the internet, check network status, and manage external storage, which are all essential for smooth automation and content management on TikTok.
  
This manifest adheres to the professional standards required for Android applications, focusing on legitimate automation practices compliant with social media platform guidelines.
